works.description: The year 2011 marked the 50th anniversary of one of the most famous and enviable cars in automotive history - the Jaguar E-Type - an icon of British motoring. Back in 1964, a Low Drag lightweight Jaguar E-Type met with a crash at the Montlhery circuit in France. The crash took the lives of the driver Peter Lindner, along with another driver and two marshals. At that time, it was thought that it won’t be ever possible to restore the car.
